<i>SOPHIE: (SINGING) I have a dream</i>

00:59.651 --> 01:02.695
<i>A song to sing</i>

01:04.441 --> 01:09.035
<i>To help me cope</i>

01:09.119 --> 01:12.205
<i>With anything</i>

01:14.707 --> 01:19.254
<i>If you see the wonder</i>

01:19.337 --> 01:23.925
<i>Of a fairy tale</i>

01:24.008 --> 01:26.970
<i>You can take the future</i>

01:30.432 --> 01:32.100
Even if you fail.

01:37.480 --> 01:40.066
Sam Carmichael.

01:40.150 --> 01:41.609
Bill Anderson.

01:44.946 --> 01:46.406
Harry Bright.

01:46.781 --> 01:48.116
(MOTORCYCLE REVVING)

01:58.668 --> 02:00.003
Gentlemen, I have to go.

02:00.086 --> 02:02.964
Thank you very much. Take care.

02:04.257 --> 02:05.717
(DOG BARKING)

02:09.679 --> 02:11.264
Morning, Rodney.

02:29.949 --> 02:31.201
Taxi!

02:31.284 --> 02:32.535
(WHOOPING SOFTLY)

02:33.203 --> 02:35.705
JFK, please, as quick as you can.

02:36.372 --> 02:37.916
(WHOOPING)

02:56.393 --> 02:57.477
(SCREAMING)

02:57.560 --> 02:58.603
(ALL EXCLAIMING)

02:58.686 --> 03:02.899
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!

03:03.108 --> 03:04.734
(ALL LAUGHING)

03:08.071 --> 03:09.948
I missed you. Oh, no...

03:10.031 --> 03:11.449
- We're...
- We're...

03:11.533 --> 03:13.535
ALL: Sophie, Ali, Lisa!
We're the greatest, bestest mates!

03:13.618 --> 03:14.661
- I'm tough.
- I'm tall.

03:14.744 --> 03:16.663
- I'm tiny.
- ALL: And we're gonna rock this place.

03:19.624 --> 03:23.795
- Sophie, it's beautiful.
- I want one.

03:23.878 --> 03:25.171
He did well, didn't he?

03:25.255 --> 03:27.048
I'm getting married tomorrow.

03:27.132 --> 03:28.341
I'm so glad you're here,

03:28.425 --> 03:33.179
because I have a secret
and I can't tell anybody else.

03:33.263 --> 03:37.183
- Sophie, you're knocked up?
- No! No! No!

03:38.393 --> 03:40.520
I've invited my dad to my wedding.

03:40.645 --> 03:42.313
You are joking!

03:42.397 --> 03:46.109
- You found him at last?
- No! No, no, no, no, no, not exactly.

03:48.820 --> 03:53.950
Okay. You know what my mom always said
when I asked about my father.

03:54.033 --> 03:56.119
It was a summer romance,

03:56.202 --> 03:59.456
and he'd gone long before she realised
that she was expecting me.

03:59.539 --> 04:02.709
And I'd always kind of accepted that
that's all I'd ever know.

04:02.792 --> 04:06.796
Well, I was ransacking some old trunks
and I found this.

04:08.465 --> 04:11.259
It's the diary she kept
the year she was pregnant with me.

04:11.342 --> 04:13.762
Sophie!

04:13.845 --> 04:17.932
"July 17th. What a night!"

04:18.016 --> 04:20.226
- I don't know if I want to hear this!
- I do!

04:20.310 --> 04:22.854
"Sam rowed me over to the little island."

04:22.937 --> 04:25.482
That's here. That's Kalokairi.

04:25.565 --> 04:29.027
"We danced on the beach,
and we kissed on the beach,

04:29.110 --> 04:31.780
"and dot, dot, dot."

04:31.863 --> 04:32.947
What?

04:33.031 --> 04:36.451
"Dot, dot, dot."
That's what they did in the olden days.

04:36.785 --> 04:37.660
Stop it!

04:38.745 --> 04:41.873
"Sam's the one. I know he is.

04:41.956 --> 04:44.417
"I've never felt like this before."

04:44.584 --> 04:46.127
<i>(HONEY HONEY</i> PLAYING)

04:46.211 --> 04:47.253
(SINGING) <i>Honey, honey</i>

04:47.337 --> 04:50.924
<i>How he thrills me</i>
<i>Honey, honey</i>

04:53.009 --> 04:54.094
<i>Honey, honey</i>

04:54.177 --> 04:57.931
<i>Nearly kills me</i>
<i>Honey, honey</i>

04:59.307 --> 05:02.644
<i>I've heard about him before</i>

05:02.727 --> 05:06.106
<i>I wanted to know some more</i>

05:06.189 --> 05:08.400
<i>And now I know what they mean</i>

05:08.483 --> 05:11.444
<i>He's a love machine</i>

05:11.528 --> 05:13.321
<i>Oh, he makes me dizzy</i>

05:15.198 --> 05:18.743
<i>Honey, honey</i>
<i>Let me feel it</i>

05:18.827 --> 05:20.203
<i>Honey, honey</i>

05:22.247 --> 05:25.667
<i>Honey, honey</i>
<i>Don't conceal it</i>

05:25.750 --> 05:27.127
<i>Honey, honey</i>

05:28.461 --> 05:30.130
<i>The way that you kiss good night</i>

05:30.213 --> 05:32.048
<i>The way that you kiss me good night</i>

05:32.132 --> 05:33.591
<i>The way that you hold me tight</i>

05:33.675 --> 05:35.468
<i>The way that you're holding me tight</i>

05:35.552 --> 05:37.637
<i>I feel like I wanna sing</i>

05:37.721 --> 05:40.682
<i>When you do your thing</i>

05:42.851 --> 05:46.896
- So this guy Sam's your father!
- The plot thickens.

05:46.980 --> 05:50.692
"All this time, Sam's been telling me
he loves me,

05:50.775 --> 05:52.652
"and now he's announced
that he's engaged,

05:52.736 --> 05:55.238
"so he's gone home to get married,

05:55.321 --> 05:56.948
"and I'm never going to see him again."

05:57.031 --> 05:58.283
Poor Donna.

05:58.366 --> 06:02.245
"August 4th. What a night!

06:02.328 --> 06:06.833
"Bill rented a motorboat,
and I took him over to the little island."

06:06.916 --> 06:09.502
- Bill? Sophie, wait.
- Hang on.

06:10.628 --> 06:13.673
"Though I'm still obsessed with Sam,

06:13.757 --> 06:16.426
"Bill's so wild. He's such a funny guy.

06:16.509 --> 06:18.344
"One thing led to another,

06:18.428 --> 06:19.554
"and dot, dot, dot."

06:19.637 --> 06:20.722
(ALL EXCLAIM)

06:20.805 --> 06:23.516
"August 11th.
Harry turned up, out of the blue,

06:23.600 --> 06:26.436
"so I said I'd show him the island.

06:26.519 --> 06:29.689
"He's so sweet and understanding,
I couldn't help it and

06:29.773 --> 06:31.357
- "dot, dot, dot!"
- Dot, dot, dot!

06:31.441 --> 06:34.861
- Oh, my God!
- (SINGSONGING) Here come the bridesmaids.

06:34.944 --> 06:37.447
Donna!

06:37.530 --> 06:40.408
DONNA: Look at you!

06:40.492 --> 06:42.952
God! Stop growing!

06:44.662 --> 06:48.124
- You sound like you're having fun already.
- Oh, we are.

06:48.208 --> 06:49.876
I used to have fun.

06:49.959 --> 06:51.336
Oh, we know!

06:54.881 --> 06:58.343
<i>SOPHIE: (SINGING) Honey, honey</i>
<i>Touch me, baby</i>

06:58.426 --> 07:00.303
<i>Honey, honey</i>

07:01.763 --> 07:05.058
<i>Honey, honey</i>
<i>Hold me, baby</i>

07:05.141 --> 07:06.518
<i>Honey, honey</i>

07:07.894 --> 07:11.398
<i>You look like a movie star</i>

07:11.481 --> 07:14.984
<i>But I love just who you are</i>

07:15.068 --> 07:17.153
<i>And, honey, to say the least</i>

07:17.237 --> 07:19.781
<i>You're a doggone beast</i>

07:19.906 --> 07:21.533
(BOTH YELLING)

07:23.701 --> 07:24.869
Bugger!

07:25.662 --> 07:27.539
My sentiments exactly.

07:32.252 --> 07:33.628
So, who is your dad?

07:33.711 --> 07:35.714
- Sam, Bill or Harry?
- I don't know.

07:35.797 --> 07:38.007
But which one did you invite?

07:38.675 --> 07:42.011
- Oh, my God!
- Oh, my God!

07:44.013 --> 07:46.307
- Do they know?
- What would you write to a total stranger?

07:46.391 --> 07:49.310
"Please come to my wedding,
you might be my father"? No.

07:49.394 --> 07:52.981
They think that Mom sent the invites,
and with what's in here,

07:53.064 --> 07:55.066
no surprise they said yes!

07:55.233 --> 07:56.609
(EXCLAIMING)

07:57.569 --> 08:00.905
<i>Honey, honey</i>
<i>How you thrill me</i>

08:00.989 --> 08:02.407
<i>Honey, honey</i>

08:04.409 --> 08:07.746
<i>Honey, honey</i>
<i>Nearly kill me</i>

08:07.829 --> 08:09.247
<i>Honey, honey</i>

08:10.874 --> 08:14.127
<i>I'd heard about you before</i>

08:14.919 --> 08:19.007
<i>I wanted to know some more</i>

08:19.090 --> 08:22.093
<i>And now I'm about to see</i>

08:22.177 --> 08:27.015
<i>What you mean to me</i>

08:29.934 --> 08:33.354
I'm trying to get to Kalokairi.
When's the next ferry?

08:34.438 --> 08:36.149
(SPEAKS GREEK)

08:36.232 --> 08:37.734
- What?
- Monday.

08:38.818 --> 08:41.821
- Bollocks!
- Yeah, my sentiments exactly.

08:44.407 --> 08:45.950
Bride or groom?

08:46.451 --> 08:49.412
Bride, although I've actually never met her.

08:49.621 --> 08:51.039
BILL: Ahoy, there.

08:52.415 --> 08:54.834
You guys need a ride to Kalokairi?

08:57.504 --> 09:03.885
Excuse me, coming through.
I have a senior citizen with me. Thank you.

09:03.968 --> 09:06.638
My mother needs a perch.

09:06.721 --> 09:08.640
Mother? We're the same age.

09:08.723 --> 09:11.643
Yeah. Well, parts of us are.

09:12.811 --> 09:13.853
(GRUNTS)

09:14.896 --> 09:16.147
Sailor.

09:18.024 --> 09:19.317
No.

09:20.193 --> 09:21.736
(THANKS IN GREEK)

09:22.737 --> 09:23.780
(SIGHS)

09:28.159 --> 09:29.994
TANYA: Oh, he has your book!

09:31.204 --> 09:32.705
(CHUCKLING) Oh...

09:33.873 --> 09:35.583
Stavros, Stavros.

09:36.084 --> 09:37.127
Stavros.

09:46.428 --> 09:47.721
(SCREAMING)

09:48.388 --> 09:50.014
It's just a fish.

09:51.850 --> 09:53.184
You are so clever.

09:53.268 --> 09:55.687
We're going to look fabulous tomorrow.

09:55.770 --> 09:59.315
I want the perfect wedding,
and I want my father to give me away.

09:59.399 --> 10:01.443
Better be a wide aisle.

10:01.526 --> 10:04.362
I will know my father as soon as I see him.

10:06.114 --> 10:08.283
LISA: Sky! Come here, gorgeous.

10:08.366 --> 10:10.201
SKY: Put me down.
I'm getting married tomorrow.

10:10.285 --> 10:11.619
Please be careful.

10:11.703 --> 10:13.705
LISA: So?
SOPHIE: There are pins in the dresses.

10:13.788 --> 10:15.457
What do you think?

10:16.166 --> 10:17.542
Oh, yes!

10:17.625 --> 10:19.294
"Oh, yes." If you had your way,

10:19.377 --> 10:22.213
it'd be a three-minute wedding
in jeans and T-shirts,

10:22.297 --> 10:24.007
washed down with a bottle of beer.

10:24.090 --> 10:26.301
You make me sound so unromantic!

10:26.384 --> 10:28.261
I just thought we should save
our money for travelling.

10:28.344 --> 10:30.180
Well, we're not going anywhere yet.

10:30.263 --> 10:33.224
Anyway, please leave. We're very, very busy.

10:33.308 --> 10:35.268
I'm just getting some props for tonight.

10:35.351 --> 10:36.436
LISA AND ALl: Ooh!

10:36.519 --> 10:38.897
SOPHIE: For his bachelor party.

10:42.067 --> 10:44.402
Why haven't you told him
you've invited your dads?

10:44.486 --> 10:46.738
Because he would say that
I'd have to tell my mom.

10:46.821 --> 10:48.907
Donna's absolutely gonna kill you
when she finds out.

10:48.990 --> 10:51.910
By the time she finds out, it'll be too late.

10:53.286 --> 10:56.081
I feel like there's a part of me missing,

10:57.624 --> 10:59.584
and when I meet my dad,

11:02.253 --> 11:06.716
everything will fall into place.

11:12.097 --> 11:13.681
(BILL EXCLAIMS)

11:13.765 --> 11:15.892
BILL: More open!
HARRY: I'm on it. I'm on it.

11:15.975 --> 11:17.352
That's good.

11:19.396 --> 11:20.563
That's it.

11:28.947 --> 11:30.740
Come on, Cleopatra.

11:37.205 --> 11:38.289
(SHRIEKS)

11:38.373 --> 11:39.416
My shoe!

11:44.003 --> 11:46.798
Will you look at what the tide washed in?

11:48.383 --> 11:53.096
- For one night.
- And one night only.

11:53.179 --> 11:59.102
- Donna and the Dynamos!
- Donna and the Dynamos!

11:59.185 --> 12:00.854
(ALL SCREAMING)

12:07.110 --> 12:09.028
Look at you!

12:09.112 --> 12:11.364
- You baby!
- Look at you!

12:11.448 --> 12:12.782
You look fantastic!

12:12.866 --> 12:14.075
You look like an old hippie!

12:14.159 --> 12:15.952
She looks fab.

12:16.035 --> 12:18.288
These are new, though.
Where did you get these?

12:18.371 --> 12:20.623
Husband number three!

12:20.707 --> 12:24.210
- Dynamos! Dynamite!
- Dynamos! Dynamite!

12:24.294 --> 12:26.171
ALL: Sleep all day and...

12:26.254 --> 12:28.006
(WHOOP) All night!

12:28.089 --> 12:29.132
(ALL LAUGHING)

12:34.804 --> 12:36.973
TANYA: So, any men at this wedding?

12:37.057 --> 12:39.517
Gorgeous Greeks of independent means?

12:39.601 --> 12:42.854
Here we go! Husband number four!

12:42.937 --> 12:46.733
- No! Not for me, for her!
- He's coming!

12:46.816 --> 12:49.194
For her, now that her book is a bestseller,

12:49.277 --> 12:52.864
and she's got the whole world
stuffing, what,

12:52.947 --> 12:56.910
mushrooms? Various vegetables?

12:56.993 --> 12:58.870
It's time to find Mr Right!

12:58.953 --> 13:01.998
Oh, please. Boring!

13:02.082 --> 13:05.043
Great couple of role models
you two are for Sophie!

13:05.126 --> 13:08.129
A serial bride and a little hermit over here!

13:09.047 --> 13:11.633
That's me! I'm a lone wolf!

13:12.300 --> 13:14.135
(HOWLING)

13:15.720 --> 13:18.848
ROSIE: So, when are the lovebirds
flying the nest?

13:18.932 --> 13:22.102
DONNA: Oh, God! Who knows?

13:22.185 --> 13:26.815
You know, I do not know what is going on
in that child's head sometimes.

13:26.898 --> 13:29.484
She wants a big white wedding, and

13:29.567 --> 13:32.529
she and Sky are making
all kinds of plans for the hotel.

13:32.612 --> 13:34.697
Sometimes I think they'll never leave.

13:34.781 --> 13:37.242
Yeah, but do you really want her to?

13:37.325 --> 13:39.702
Well, I want what's best for her.

13:39.911 --> 13:40.954
Of course not!

13:41.037 --> 13:42.080
(ALL LAUGHING)

13:43.123 --> 13:46.459
Sky! Come meet my backup girls.

13:46.543 --> 13:48.420
ROSIE: Backup girls, my ass!
TANYA: Backup girls, my ass!

13:48.503 --> 13:50.380
He's the leading man at tomorrow's shindig.

13:50.463 --> 13:52.090
- SKY: The lucky man.
- Hello.

13:52.173 --> 13:54.676
- You must be Rosie.
- I am.

13:54.759 --> 13:56.720
- How are you?
- Very well.

13:57.762 --> 13:59.597
And you must be Tanya.

14:00.014 --> 14:03.601
- I've heard so much about you.
- All bad, I hope.

14:03.685 --> 14:05.103
- Yes.
- And all true.

14:05.186 --> 14:06.438
Donna... Here, let me get them.

14:08.773 --> 14:12.110
I know who you are.
You're Bill Anderson, aren't you?

14:14.279 --> 14:17.866
<i>- Bloke in a Boat in Botswana.</i>
- Yes, I am.

14:17.949 --> 14:21.119
You know, your books are a godsend
on dull business trips.

14:21.202 --> 14:24.038
Now, I may look like I'm pondering
my securities, but in reality,

14:24.122 --> 14:28.752
I'm trekking across
some remote corner of the planet.

14:28.835 --> 14:30.795
You should try it for real sometime.

14:30.879 --> 14:33.923
No, certainly, I'll never be
the spontaneous adventurer.

14:34.007 --> 14:38.261
- You're a close friend of Donna's?
- No, I haven't heard from her for 20 years.

14:38.344 --> 14:41.014
- SAM: Really?
- And then this invite, out of the blue.

14:41.097 --> 14:42.849
You know, that's a coincidence,
neither had I.

14:42.932 --> 14:45.477
- Going about!
- You got it!

14:45.560 --> 14:50.857
Right. Wait...
I've got it. Fine. Fine.

14:52.859 --> 14:55.487
ROSIE: You should have brought
the iron lung.

14:55.612 --> 14:58.073
Why did I wear stilettos?

14:58.865 --> 15:00.950
- (GASPING) Oxygen.
- Oh, my God!

15:02.577 --> 15:04.871
- Auntie Rosie!
- Hey, hey!

15:04.954 --> 15:09.292
- Look at Sophie. She's gotten so beautiful!
- I know.

15:09.375 --> 15:11.795
ROSIE: Come here to me.

15:13.296 --> 15:20.220
Sophie Sheridan, you get more gorgeous
every time I see you. You do.

15:20.303 --> 15:24.307
- I bet you don't remember me.
- Not with all that plastic surgery.

15:25.016 --> 15:28.728
Of course I do, Auntie Tanya.
You haven't changed at all.

15:30.063 --> 15:31.147
- I'm so happy for you.
- Look at my baby,

15:31.231 --> 15:33.900
her whole life ahead of her.

15:33.983 --> 15:39.239
Oh, please, I'm getting married.
I'm not joining a convent!

15:39.322 --> 15:41.324
- She's feisty. I love that.
- Yeah.

15:41.408 --> 15:43.701
She's a chip off the old block.

15:44.494 --> 15:47.664
If she were more like me,
she wouldn't be getting married at 20.

15:47.747 --> 15:49.416
Or married at all.

15:50.500 --> 15:53.670
I meant to get the laundry down
before you came.

15:53.753 --> 15:54.796
ROSIE: Tanya's going home!

15:54.879 --> 15:57.841
And you'd think with all this
new technology,

15:57.924 --> 16:00.885
they would figure out a machine
that would make the beds.

16:00.969 --> 16:03.221
And if they did,
you'd be going along behind it,

16:03.304 --> 16:04.639
making them again.

16:04.723 --> 16:06.349
I know you, Mom.

16:07.559 --> 16:11.479
But I am good at modern...
Tell them about the Internets.

16:11.563 --> 16:13.690
- He's gonna put me on the line.
- SOPHIE: Online.

16:13.773 --> 16:15.150
SKY: I'm designing a website.

16:15.233 --> 16:19.404
I just think this place has so much potential,
and no one knows we're here.

16:19.487 --> 16:23.867
So, if I market it really, really well, then,
hopefully, people will come flooding in.

16:23.950 --> 16:27.871
We just want this to be
the ultimate romantic destination.

16:27.954 --> 16:30.331
This was once supposed to be
the site of Aphrodite's fountain,

16:30.415 --> 16:32.917
you know, the goddess of love.
And if you drank the water,

16:33.001 --> 16:35.712
you were supposed to find true love
and perfect happiness.

16:35.795 --> 16:38.715
- I'll have a glass of that.
- Yeah, I'll have a bucket.

16:38.798 --> 16:40.675
<i>TANYA: Aphrodite's spa?</i>

16:40.759 --> 16:43.261
Well, I thought you didn't want
boatloads of tourists.

16:43.386 --> 16:45.388
Oh, no, not boatloads, no.

16:45.472 --> 16:48.892
But, you know, a few more would be nice.

16:50.268 --> 16:54.230
Okay, now, the thing about the toilet,

16:54.314 --> 16:59.402
if it doesn't flush right away, just go
and come back in a while, and it should...

17:00.570 --> 17:03.073
Nothing works around here, except for me.

17:03.156 --> 17:07.410
I've been running this hotel for 15 years,
and I have never had a day off.

17:07.493 --> 17:08.744
Oh, my God! Sorry.

17:08.828 --> 17:09.871
(EXCLAIMING)

17:10.246 --> 17:11.289
<i>(MONEY, MONEY, MONEY</i> PLAYING)

17:11.372 --> 17:12.582
(SINGING) <i>I work all night</i>
<i>I work all day</i>

17:12.665 --> 17:15.919
<i>To pay the bills I have to pay</i>

17:16.002 --> 17:17.420
ALL: <i>Ain't it sad?</i>

17:18.630 --> 17:20.423
<i>And still there never seems to be</i>

17:20.507 --> 17:22.925
<i>A single penny left for me</i>

17:23.009 --> 17:24.094
Don't sit down there.

17:24.176 --> 17:25.261
<i>That's too bad</i>

17:25.345 --> 17:26.721
It's broken.

17:26.805 --> 17:30.934
<i>In my dreams</i>
<i>I have a plan</i>

17:31.017 --> 17:34.437
<i>If I got me a wealthy man</i>

17:34.521 --> 17:36.189
<i>I wouldn't have to work at all</i>

17:36.272 --> 17:41.319
<i>I'd fool around and have a ball</i>

