a spontaneous holiday.

29:13.470 --> 29:14.512
Uh-huh.

29:15.180 --> 29:17.474
I just dropped in to say hi.

29:18.016 --> 29:20.351
(STAMMERING) Okay. What is this?

29:20.435 --> 29:24.314
It's one of those serendipitous moments
in life when three complete strangers

29:24.397 --> 29:26.316
share a common thought.

29:27.692 --> 29:28.985
Strangers?

29:29.861 --> 29:33.656
- You don't know each other?
- That's generally the definition.

29:33.865 --> 29:36.826
Okay, good, but who... Why are you here?

29:36.910 --> 29:39.204
Who said that you could
stay up in my old goat-house?

29:39.287 --> 29:40.830
- BILL: Didn't catch the name.
- Greek lady.

29:40.914 --> 29:42.665
- Well, she spoke Greek.
- Yeah.

29:42.749 --> 29:44.918
Or maybe she said we couldn't
stay in the old goat-house.

29:45.001 --> 29:47.003
- Yeah, maybe that was it, in Greek.
- There you go.

29:47.087 --> 29:49.672
Yeah, that's it, that's it.
You can't stay here because

29:49.756 --> 29:52.717
I'm closed and I'm full.

29:52.801 --> 29:56.638
And I'm busy, I'm really...
I have a wedding, my...

29:56.721 --> 29:58.139
Local girl's getting married...

29:58.223 --> 29:59.516
Donna. Donna, don't worry about us.

29:59.599 --> 30:01.059
Bill here is used to roughing it.

30:01.142 --> 30:03.686
- And Harry here...
- I'm spontaneous.

30:03.770 --> 30:05.146
- Spontaneous.
- DONNA: Ah.

30:07.357 --> 30:09.067
What about you?

30:09.150 --> 30:11.361
Just wanted to see the island.

30:11.861 --> 30:14.072
You know what it meant to me.

30:16.241 --> 30:19.452
Okay, I'm gonna arrange for a boat

30:19.536 --> 30:23.039
