30:23.123 --> 30:25.125
- I have a boat, Donna.
- You have a boat?

30:25.208 --> 30:26.543
Good, get on it,

30:26.626 --> 30:27.836
and anchors away.

30:27.919 --> 30:29.921
- Hey, Donna...
- Away, away.

30:30.547 --> 30:32.340
ALL: It's good to see you.

30:32.424 --> 30:33.466
(SIGHS)

30:39.723 --> 30:42.726
Now, baby, this should
tickle your taste buds.

30:42.809 --> 30:46.020
Down, big fella.
I'm old enough to be your mother.

30:46.312 --> 30:47.731
ROSIE: (STIFLING SNICKER) Grandmother.

30:48.273 --> 30:49.357
Where's Sophie?

30:49.482 --> 30:52.569
- I think she went down to the beach.
- What's up?

30:56.531 --> 30:58.074
(CRYING)

31:01.578 --> 31:02.787
ROSIE: Donna?

31:06.124 --> 31:08.251
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

31:08.668 --> 31:10.003
(DONNA CRYING SOFTLY)

31:10.086 --> 31:11.129
(KNOCKS)

31:12.964 --> 31:14.382
(BLOWS NOSE)

31:14.758 --> 31:16.217
(WHISPERING) Talk to her.

31:18.386 --> 31:22.307
(SINGING) <i>Chiquitita, tell me what's wrong</i>

31:23.099 --> 31:25.769
(WHIMPERING)

31:26.352 --> 31:28.229
Oh, me.

31:29.189 --> 31:33.777
(SINGING) <i>I have never seen such sorrow</i>

31:36.780 --> 31:40.992
BOTH: <i>In your eyes</i>

31:41.534 --> 31:46.247
<i>And the wedding is tomorrow</i>

31:48.917 --> 31:53.296
<i>How I hate to see you like this</i>

31:53.380 --> 31:58.134
<i>There is no way you can deny it</i>

31:58.218 --> 32:02.347
BOTH: <i>I can see</i>

32:02.430 --> 32:04.891
<i>That you're oh, so sad</i>

32:04.974 --> 32:06.976
<i>So quiet</i>

32:11.022 --> 32:15.777
<i>Chiquitita, tell me the truth</i>

32:16.653 --> 32:21.908
<i>I'm a shoulder you can cry on</i>

32:23.993 --> 32:27.664
<i>Your best friend</i>

32:27.997 --> 32:32.252
<i>I'm the one you must rely on</i>

32:33.837 --> 32:37.173
<i>You were always sure of yourself</i>

32:39.426 --> 32:43.513
<i>Now I see you've broken a feather</i>

32:47.016 --> 32:53.189
<i>I hope we can patch it up</i>

32:53.314 --> 32:54.983
<i>Together</i>

32:56.651 --> 33:02.282
<i>Chiquitita, you and I know</i>

33:02.365 --> 33:04.492
<i>How the heartaches come and they go</i>

33:04.576 --> 33:08.288
<i>And the scars, they're leaving</i>

33:08.371 --> 33:11.666
<i>You'll be dancing once again</i>

33:11.750 --> 33:14.502
<i>And the pain will end</i>

33:14.586 --> 33:18.506
<i>You will have no time for grieving</i>

33:20.216 --> 33:25.805
<i>Chiquitita, you and I cry</i>

33:25.889 --> 33:28.099
<i>But the sun is still in the sky</i>

33:28.183 --> 33:31.895
<i>And shining above you</i>

33:31.978 --> 33:35.190
<i>Let me hear you sing once more</i>

33:35.273 --> 33:38.026
<i>Like you did before</i>

33:38.109 --> 33:42.113
<i>Sing a new song, Chiquitita</i>

33:44.240 --> 33:46.910
<i>Try once more</i>

33:46.993 --> 33:49.412
<i>Like I did before</i>

33:50.497 --> 33:52.165
<i>Sing a new song</i>

33:54.084 --> 33:56.086
- It's her dad.
- Whose dad?

33:57.087 --> 33:58.546
Sophie's dad.

34:01.591 --> 34:04.594
Remember how I said it was Sam?
Sam the architect,

34:04.677 --> 34:06.262
who had to go home to get married?

34:06.346 --> 34:09.641
I'm not sure that it was him,

34:09.724 --> 34:14.312
because there were two other guys
around the same time.

34:15.563 --> 34:18.733
Donna Sheridan. You shady lady.

34:18.817 --> 34:20.193
Why didn't you tell us?

34:20.275 --> 34:23.862
Well, I never knew that
I would ever, ever have to.

34:23.947 --> 34:27.074
I never imagined I'd see all three of them

34:27.158 --> 34:28.784
in my old goat-house

34:28.868 --> 34:31.454
